faq.question: Is attending EECS1028 lecture from Suprakash Datta worth it to pass the class? Does Suprakash Datta explain EECS1028 well?
faq.answer: Prof Datta is Overall a solid guy. The class is tough, but if you attend most of his lectures and keep up in the textbook there's no question you wont do well in the class. Only Reason hes not 5/5 is because he never ever ever returns anything on time. Expect to have everything back a month after you write it LOL. But yea solid prof .

faq.question: Will I enjoy taking Suprakash Datta's class for EECS3214 and what kind of prof are they? Should I attend EECS3214 lectures with Suprakash Datta? Does Suprakash Datta explain EECS3214 well? How much time is spent studying for assignments and homework for EECS3214 with Suprakash Datta?
faq.answer: Great Professor who genuinely cares about the students and the program. Lectures are informative and follows the slides and book closely. You MUST study from the book and not (primarily) the slides. Questions are open ended (This is a good thing; too much detail for brute memorization) and assignments are fair.

faq.question: Does Suprakash Datta explain EECS3214 well? Will I need to study a lot for EECS3214 with Suprakash Datta?
faq.answer: his exam questions are far too ambiguous and open. Instead of putting questions from important parts of chapter, his questions are unknown as something too specific as a diagram or summary of entire section in a question and with so long powerpoint videos!!!! for the first time i am looking at such dense notes so it confuses as how deep to study .

faq.question: Should I take Suprakash Datta's EECS3214 class if I care about my grades and GPA? Is attending EECS3214 lecture from Suprakash Datta worth it to pass the class? Will I need to study a lot for EECS3214 with Suprakash Datta?
faq.answer: Prof doesn't provide feedback and takes forever to give grades back. His tests are so open ended. I thought his lectures were so boring, hes so monotone. His assignments weren't too hard. Try to listen to him in class even though you might be fighting the need to drift off into a deep sleep.

faq.question: Should I attend EECS3214 lectures with Suprakash Datta? Does Suprakash Datta explain EECS3214 well? Will I need to study a lot for EECS3214 with Suprakash Datta?
faq.answer: Very fair prof. Love his midterm and exam. A lot of questions have multiple solutions. If you can give something creative within the theory discussed in class you usually get full marks. Doesn't make you memorize anything, just wants to see you understand what's going on. Assignments are easy. Guaranteed credit with an honest effort.

faq.question: Is Suprakash Datta a nice professor for EECS2011? Is Suprakash Datta giving good grades for EECS2011? Is attending EECS2011 lecture from Suprakash Datta worth it to pass the class? Will I need to study a lot for EECS2011 with Suprakash Datta?
faq.answer: Lectures were pretty good. Lecture slides could've been better, but if you read the slides from other sections/years along with his, you could skip using the textbook. Assignments/tests/exam were common with James Elder's section and were fair and gave plenty of bonuses.

faq.question: Is Suprakash Datta a nice professor for EECS2011? Is Suprakash Datta giving good grades for EECS2011? Should I attend EECS2011 lectures with Suprakash Datta? Will I need to study a lot for EECS2011 with Suprakash Datta?
faq.answer: Great Prof, I really enjoyed the lectures even tho they were 3 hours long, 2011 is notoriously the hardest course in 2nd year cs but with datta I was able to understand the concepts clearly, and his test was reasonable too, assignments were challenging but useful also(we got 3 bonus marks) and exam was really easy as long as you knew your stuff.

faq.question: Is Suprakash Datta a nice professor for EECS3101?
faq.answer: I've taken EECS 3101 and Math 1019 with him and he is by far the most caring and approachable prof at York. He doesn't want people to fail his course he wants you to learn and will spend hours much past what any other prof will put in to make sure you succeed. Plus if you actually talk to him he has good stories/life advice.

faq.question: Is Suprakash Datta a nice professor for EECS1028? Is Suprakash Datta giving good grades for EECS1028?
faq.answer: Great Teacher. Hard course. May seem easy but test is very hard/ logical

faq.question: Is Suprakash Datta a nice professor for EECS1028? Is Suprakash Datta giving good grades for EECS1028? Should I attend EECS1028 lectures with Suprakash Datta? Will I need to study a lot for EECS1028 with Suprakash Datta?
faq.answer: Professor Datta is by far one of the best professors I have ever had. I had him for discrete math, which is why the difficulty level was so high. However, he takes time out of his schedule to organize study sessions before tests and he genuinely cares about his students. His lectures are extremely informative and he explains concepts very clearly.

faq.question: Is Suprakash Datta a nice professor for EECS3214? Should I attend EECS3214 lectures with Suprakash Datta? Will I need to study a lot for EECS3214 with Suprakash Datta?
faq.answer: Great prof, approachable, willing to help. In return, unforgiving w marking. Slides are from the publisher, so take this as a clue to READ THE BOOK. Assignments are fun and actually practicaluseful but difficult. Except for brief overview, coding for assignments not taught in class. U must be comfortable w coding for assignments. If not, YOUTUBE.

faq.question: Is Suprakash Datta giving good grades for EECS1028? Should I attend EECS1028 lectures with Suprakash Datta? Does Suprakash Datta explain EECS1028 well?
faq.answer: His tests are hard as hell and he almost never uses any questions from the book, so you really need to understand the material if you wanna do well. He's still a really cool guy and will go the distance to make you understand the material. Also, don't_skip_any_of_the_tutorials. Most of the exercises he covers in tutorials show up on tests.

faq.question: Is Suprakash Datta a nice professor for EECS1019? Is Suprakash Datta giving good grades for EECS1019?
faq.answer: He will go above and beyond for students who asks for help. if you are looking for good grade you MUST go to his tutorials. amazing professor highly recommended.
